@6251   = ~Chill Touch~
@6252   = ~Chill Touch

When a necromancer uses this ability, a blue glow encompasses his hand. This energy attacks the life force of any living creature upon which the wizard makes a successful melee attack. The touched creature suffers 1d4+1 points of cold damage and must save vs. Death or be Slowed and lose three points of Strength for two rounds. 

Undead touched by this energy are Held for two rounds. They do not receive a savign throw to avoid the effect.~
@6253   = ~Ghoul Touch~
@6254   = ~Ghoul Touch

When a necromancer uses this ability, a red glow encompasses his hand. On a successful touch, the spell inflicts 1d4+1 points of magic damage. If the victim fails a saving throw vs. death, the spell continues to do 1d4 damage in the second round and 1d3 damage in the third round. Furthermore, the victim is paralyzed for 1 round and infected with a disease that saps his Strength, Dexterity and Constitution by two points each for five rounds.~
@6255   = ~Vampiric Touch~
@6256   = ~Vampiric Touch

When a necromancer uses this ability, his hand is encompassed by a pale blue fire. Anyone successfully attacked by the necromancer loses 1d6+1 hit points, while the necromancer gains 1d6+1 hit points (any hit points over the caster's normal maximum treated as temporary additional hit points, lasting for 4 turns). Upon failing a saving throw vs. death with a -2 penalty, the victim loses 1d6 more hit points and also suffers a loss of 3 points of Constitution for one turn. 

Any undead touched by the necromancer while this ability is active are placed under the necromancer's control for five rounds.~
